# Kids 0-18 Integrative Pediatrics — CRM Project Rules

## Tech Stack
- Framework: Next.js 16.2.6 (App Router) — HAS BREAKING CHANGES, read node_modules/next/dist/docs/ before writing Next.js code
- Language: TypeScript 5, React 19.2.4
- Auth: NextAuth (Auth.js) v5 beta — Credentials provider + JWT sessions
- ORM: Prisma 7.8 → PostgreSQL on Supabase (pooler). Client at lib/generated/prisma
- Styling: Tailwind CSS v4 + shadcn/ui + Radix. Use class-variance-authority + tailwind-merge
- Icons: lucide-react (ONLY — no other icon libraries)
- Charts: recharts 3
- Forms: react-hook-form + zod 4 + @hookform/resolvers
- Background jobs: BullMQ 5 + ioredis → Redis
- Email: Gmail API → SendGrid → SMTP/nodemailer (priority cascade)
- Testing: Vitest 4

## Critical Rules
1. ALWAYS check what already exists in the codebase before suggesting new implementations
2. Use the existing Prisma singleton from lib/prisma.ts — NEVER create a new PrismaClient instance
3. Use shadcn/ui components from components/ui/ — NEVER install new UI libraries
4. Follow existing snake_case table/column mapping in Prisma schema
5. All new pages go under app/(dashboard)/ and use the existing layout (sidebar + header)
6. All API routes follow existing patterns in app/api/ — check a similar route first
7. Never modify auth.ts, auth.config.ts, or proxy.ts without explicit instruction
8. Encryption uses lib/crypto.ts — use it for any PII/PHI storage
9. Settings are stored in the singleton Settings table — never create new config tables
10. Notifications use the existing Notification model — just add new types

